 look at onscreen representations of rudeness, ridiculing, racist and sexist etiquettes, hospitality, table manners, and more. In doing so, it reveals etiquette to be a persistent theme in cinema and questions the role it plays in either upholding or denying the basic humanity of others.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aEtiquette in motion pictures. 0aMotion pictureszEurope. 0aMotion pictureszUnited States. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849349740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493497423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493497/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles